This is because your JavaScript code is invalid. Remember you are putting your JS code in a python string and therefore you should put 'r' before the string in order to avoid python escaping special sequences (in your case \n'):

```
temp = r'''
function utf8_encode(e) {
    e = e.replace(/\r\n/g, "\n");
    for (var g = "", k = 0; k < e.length; k++) {
        var h = e.charCodeAt(k);
        128 > h ? g += String.fromCharCode(h) : (127 < h && 2048 > h ? g += String.fromCharCode(h >> 6 | 192) : (g += String.fromCharCode(h >> 12 | 224), g += String.fromCharCode(h >> 6 & 63 | 128)), g += String.fromCharCode(h & 63 | 128))
    }
    return g
}
'''
```

