@pde, the code in `cli.py` that should guarantee that renewal behavior is triggered independent of the order in which the names are specified to the client is at

https://github.com/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/blob/master/letsencrypt/cli.py#L208

In particular, the use of `set()` is meant to guarantee that order doesn't matter here. @JohnDenker, do you have a reproducible way to trigger some other behavior in the client?

I have a group with myself and another user (for test purposes). When i add messages in the group i can create a unique ID by joining the channel id with the message ID. When I delete a message, the event object has no way to identify what group it was removed from. This does not happen with a channel (and i suspect supergroup)

```python
@client.on(events.MessageDeleted())
