After invesigating the ``jupyter-nbextension`` code a bit, I came up with this function:

```python
import os
from jupyter_core.paths import jupyter_path


def check_if_nbextension_installed(extname):
    paths = jupyter_path()

    for path in paths:
        if not os.path.exists(path):
            continue
        if 'nbextensions' not in os.listdir(path):
            continue
        if extname in os.listdir(os.path.join(path, 'nbextensions')):
            return True
    else:
        return False

check_if_nbextension_installed('jupyter-vega')
# True
```

Seems to work on my system, at least. We could use this sort of check in the [``_ipython_display_``](https://github.com/vega/ipyvega/blob/master/vega/base.py#L42) method and print a useful warning if the extension is not installed.

Maybe @carreau could comment on whether this snippet is the correct way of checking for the presence of an nbextension

